{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_jennings_ver01/data/sn95047246/00529042206/1930042501/0367.xml":{"full_text":"Capitol Group Costs Twelve Million\n\u2022As secure as the government It\nhouses\u201d was the desire of the West\nVirginians when they planned the\nState Capitol group at Charleston\n.And so they built it of stone tor\nstmngth and permanence.\nTwo wings are completed and now\nthe main building of the group is\nunder construction. It will cost ap\nproximately 85,000.000 and will com\nplete the $12,000,000 Capitol group.\nAbout 667 carloads of cut stone for\nthe third unit will be shipped from\nthe quarries of the Indiana Limestone\ncompany. Bedford. Ind. The architect\nPresident Gets Poppy\nFive-year-old Lois June Allen,\norphan daughter of a world war vet\neran, pins the first \u201cBuddy Poppy\u201d of\nthe Spring campaign on Mr. Hoover\u2019s\ncoat. The money from the sale of the\npoppies goes for the relief of disabled\nveterans and their dependants.\nLiSSKf r\u00bb\u00ab i\nI\nj rjaj^M\ni i\n/MgS^\nNEW BOOKS\nFOR\nGRADUATION j\nBUY YOUR GRADUATION\nT PRESENT AT OUR SHOP.\n\nSOME BOOKS YOU j\nSHOULD READ:\nThe Secretary\u2019s\nHandbook\n(A Manual of Correct Useage) j\nby Sarah Agusta Taintor\nElbert Hubbard\u2019s\nScrap Book\nThe Best Of My!\nMemory\nBy Payson Terhune\n^Rise Ameri\ncan Civili^ t j on\nBy Charles A Beai.\nBOOKSHOP OF THE\nTAMIAMI TRAIL\nis Cass Gilbert, who has won national\nprominence for his designs of many\nfine buildings.\nWhen completed, this all-stone\nstructure will be one of the country\u2019s\noutstanding capitals. Seeking peer\nless beauty and dignity, those respon\nsible for the design and construction\nlooked far beyond their own state for\nappropriate building materials, even\ntually approving the quarries of the\nIndiana Limestone company. The\ncapital thus joins the ranks of hun\ndreds of great public buildings every\nwhere, constructed of stone from the\nHoosier state.\nTesting Beauty\nl IB\nfl*\n\nSv rs'\nsn\nMM\u00a3. WOQ*\nBeauty is 80 per cent art. 20 per\ncent nature. In this ratio. Mme\nHelena Rubinstein of London. Paris\nand New York, an authority whcse\nopinion in such matters carries weight\non four continents, rates the two\ncontributing factors to woman\u2019s looks\n\"There Is no answer today to the\nquestion of who is the most beautiful\nwoman alive.\u201d Mme. Rubinstein main\ntains. \"With cosmetics once worth a\nQueen\u2019s ransom placed by modern\nmethods of distribution within th*\nreach of all, old barriers are broken\nWomen who would have been hope\nlessly ugly in another age make up\nin this one into striking beauties.\n\u201cArt Is a great leveler\u2014or eleva lot\n\u2014of good looks. So many women are\nbeautiful now through clever use oi\ncosmetics that none are outstanding\nMany are Individual, none superior\n\u201cThe professional beauty who wa>\nborn that way Is as dead as Fai:\nRosamond. Ninon and Helen of IToy\nThe last of her kind vanished with\nLillian Russel) and Lily Langtry. Just\nas cosmetics were coming into general\npopular use.\u201d\nr- .T THE. NAME OF YOUR. OH/ s<? YOU CALL YOUR. BtFU>\nHA mEW CANARY BIR.D/ PINKN^Z JOE 7 DoE? THAT STAND\nv for' Joseph or for., J\nlOj^; J &EPHIN ^XrffT\n1 WlO' 4OE/J\nwe don't know/ A x<x \\JV z/C- niftW\nTHAT'S WHV WE\ncall IT JOE/z JtNuLKJ O'\nt ZrR nV\n\"7/ \\T BP\nE\nSb\u00df\u00ae TS<\u00bb *W 111 T Af \u00ab*~ysv SCHOOL.MtrM.su\n2/Vw/ 'W I HAVE A LITTLE 006 NAMEP\nIlli z<X x- ti >pot\nt ST n /Jr whenever, i call him\nO HE l\u00a3 ON THE DOT\nBILL PROVIDES *5,704,300\nk FOR FLORIDA WORK\nWashington, April 21.\u2014Florida\nprojects totaling $5,704,300 are\ncontained in the omnibus rivers\nand harbors bill introduced in the\nhouse today by Chairman Demp\nsey of the rivers and harbors com\nmittee. The measure carries ap\nproximately $110,000,000.\nThe measure carried $4,066,-\n000 for construction work in the\nCaloosahatchee river and Lake\nOkeechobee drainage areas, after\na final revision had been made\nprior to introduction. As revised\nthe provision relating to the drain\nage areas provided that the le\nvees be constructed to an eleva\ntion of 31 feet above sea level,\nbut that they should be so built\nas to be capable of being raised\nthe additional three feet.\n\u2022The section also provided that\nthe federal government perform\nall work of construction of the\nlevees, that the state of Florida\nor other local interests contribute\n$4,546,000 toward the cost and\nthat the federal government in\ncur no expense in acquiring prop\nerty for the letfees.\nThere is also a provision in the\nbill as introduced today provid\ning for a survey of waterways\nacross south Georgia and north\nFlorida connecting the Atlantic\nintracoastal waterways with the\nproposed gulf intracoastal water\nway along what is described as\nthe \u201cmost practical route.\u201d\nOther important Florida sur\nveys included:\nWaterway across from Pensa\ncola bay to the Caloosahatchee\nriver and for a cross-Florida east\ncoast canal; the Miami river and\nthe waterway from Miami to Key\nWest, with a view to constructing\nan extension to the intercoastal\nwaterway from Jacksonville to\nMiami.\nFlorida projects and those in\nGeorgia and Alabama directly\naffecting Florida, follow:\nCaloosahatchee river and Lake\nOkeechobee drainage areas, $4,-\n066,000.\nMiami river, $BOO,OOO.\nTampa harbor, $239,200.\nHollywood harbor and Miami\nharbor, $200,000.\nSt. John\u2019s river from Jackson\nville to the ocean, $lll,OOO.\nIntracoastal waterway from\nPensacola bay to Mobile bay,\n$lOO,OOO.\nSt. John\u2019s river from Palatka\nto Lake Carney, $63,000.\nInland waterway from Cape\nFear river to St. Johns river,\nShipyard river, S. C., $46,000.\nSt. Petersburg harbor, $45,-\nooo'\nCharlotte harbor, $22,500.\nSt. Mark\u2019s river, $ll,OOO.\nEast Pass channel, Choctawat\nchee bay, $6OO.\nSavannah harbor, Ga., $237,-\n000; Savannah river,' below Au\ngusta, Ga., $1,305,000; Bruns\nwick harbor, Ga., $394,000; in\ntracoastal waterway, from Mobile\nbay, Ala., to New Orleans, La.,\n$20,000; Gulfport harbor, Miss.,\n$200,000; Biloxi harbor, Miss.,\n$52,000; Mobile harbor, Ala.,\n$478,000; channel between Mo\nbile bay, Ala., and Mississippi\nsound, Ala., $55,000.\nNOYES AGAIN HEADS\nASSOCIATED PRESS\nNew York, April 22.\u2014Frank B.\nNoyes of Washington, president of\nthe. Associated Press since 1900,\nwas re-elected today by the board\nof directors at their meeting fol\nlowing yesterday\u2019s conference.\nTHE BROOKSVILLE JOURNAL\nMANUFACTURERS\nFRIGIDAIRES ANTICIPATE\nGREAT SUMMER TRADE\nDay ton, 0., April 17.\u2014Prosperi\nty being experienced by the electric\nrefrigeration industry as prepara\ntions go forward for the heavy\nsummer buying season is being re\nflected in other lines. As an ex\nample, Frigidaire Corporation has\njust received a shipment of Ger\nman hygrometers, comprising the\nentire American supply of these\nhumidity recording instruments.\nConfidence that all records of his\ncompany will be broken during the\npresent year was expressed by E.\nG. Biechler, president and general\nmanager, who pointed out that\nduring March more than twice as\nmany people visited the company's\nshowrooms throughout the country\nas during the same month in 1929.\n\u201cThe outlook is most encourag\ning,\u201d Mr. Biechler said. \u201cFirst\nquarter production records were far\nahead of the same period last year,\nwith more men employed in our\nfactories than there were during\nthe same period last year. We face\nthe approaching buying season\nwith every confidence that all rec\nords will be broken.\u201d\nAs conclusive evidence of its at\ntitude toward the current business\noutlook, Frigidaire Corporation\nhas launched a million dollar news\npaper advertising campaign which\nwill be conducted until early sum\nmer to point outstanding features\nof its products. Features to be\nstressed include surplus power,\nwith ability to freeze ice cubes\nquickly, and maintain temperatures\nbelow 50 degrees, even during the\nhottest weather.\n\u201cAbility to perform satisfactorily\nin extreme heat is the real test of\nan electric refrigerator,\u201d Mr.\nBiechler said, \u201cjust as ability to\nkeep the home comfortable in zero\nweather is the real test of a fur\nnace\u2019s efficiency. Ability of Frig\nidaire to maintain its even, unvary\ning temperature under the most\nsevere tests has always been an\noutstanding feature.\n\u201cSuch advantages as those afford\ned by the cold control, the hydrator\nAnd the convenient flat top will be\nbrought to public attention. All\nporcelain-on-steel, inside and out, a\nlife time finish as easily cleaned as\na china dish, is another point. El\nevated food shelves and quiet oper\nation are other refinements upon\nwhich we are counting to help\nmake this year another record\nbreaker.\n\u201cReliability is a feature for which\nFrigidaire is famous. Frigidaire\nis sold with a definite guarantee,\nbacked by General Motors. Still\nmore important to the purchaser is\nthe fact that year after year Frigi\ndaire continues to give satisfaction\n\u2014long after the guarantee has ex\npired. If service should be re\nquired, it is rendered instantly and\nwithout removing the machine\nfrom the premises.\n\u201cThese are a few of the reasons\nwhich have influenced people to\nbuy more than three times as many\nFrigidaires as any other make of\nelectric refrigerator.\u201d\nSENATE CONFIRMS\nCUBBERLY NOMINATION\nWashington, April 22. The\nnomination of Fred Cubberly to be\nUnited States attorney for the\nnorthern district of Florida was\nconfirmed today by the Senate.\nMove along with the world\u2014or\nit will move along without\nyou.\nMiss Annie Snow spend the\nPERCOLATOR\nA most beautiful ta\nble appointment at a\nvery reasonable price.\nThis famous Hot\npoint percolator makes\ncoffee by the Hotpoint\nHot-Drip method \u2014al-\nways clear, aromatic\nand satisfying. Other\nstyles up to $35.00.\nSpecial 30-Day Sale\nThe Potpoint Bor\ndeaux PERCOLAT\nOR $l2 00 value can\nnow be had for $9.95.\nTerms $1.95 down\nand balance $2.00 per\nmonth with your elec\ntric bill.\nLet our salesmen tell\nyou about the special\ncombination offer.\nFLORIDA POWER\nCorporation\nTelephone 212\nBrooksville, Fla.\nj/z, AmHTV\nV MONARCH r-fcpaM\nEx\ni fl\nJig?.\".' AM,. \u25a0M^'- MH lux J/i ^SSBK\nV\\ \\xXcN.. II II\nMK..V.\n'Wwl Um Hifo' ^M 'MH\nwism\nWE \u00a9EFER\nThe MAJESTIC RADIO At $116.50 To $225.50 COMPLETE ||l|\nMajestic Dealers Lead Inhales. I\nIn 1929, you saw Majestic dealers get nearly one-third of\nall the electric radio sales in the country. You saw Ma\njestic dealers average 25 sales every time the 54 compet\ning lines averaged one sale each. In 1930 you will see\n\neven more amazing things as you watch Majestic.\nPrices Are Guaranteed Until 1931. So come in and let\nus talk to you about our easy terms.\nROGER\u2019S Department Store I\nDon\u2019t Fail To See the Flower Show At The Tangerine Hotel\nMay 1\nFIRST NATIONAL BANK\nIn\nBROOKSVILLE, FLORIDA\nMember of Federal\nReserve System.\nU. S. Depository for\nPostal Savings\nF. B. Coogler, President\nJohn Patterson, Cashier\n^ONT HAVE Shabby\nnow sand and refinish floors!\nthem yourself for of\nHave you seen the new\nprofessional costs Johnson home floor\nL sander? Drop in and let\nus tell you about it\nRussel] Hardware Company\n10 S. Main St. Phone 51","height":"22772","width":"15960"}}
